    <h1 id="bookh1">Prenatal Care - 4th Month</h1>
    
    <h3>Nutrition</h3>
    <p>
        In the 4th month of pregnancy, your baby continues to grow. Maintain a healthy diet to support their development. Consider the following:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Continue to include a variety of nutrient-rich foods in your diet.</li>
        <li>Increase your intake of calcium for strong bones and teeth. Dairy products and leafy greens are good sources.</li>
        <li>Ensure you're getting enough iron to prevent anemia. Foods like lean red meat, beans, and spinach can help.</li>
        <li>Consume plenty of fiber to prevent constipation, including whole grains and fresh fruits.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Exercises</h3>
    <p>
        Staying active in the 4th month is important for both your health and your baby's. Here are some safe exercises to consider:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Low-impact aerobic exercises like swimming or stationary cycling can help maintain cardiovascular fitness.</li>
        <li>Yoga and stretching exercises can relieve tension and improve flexibility.</li>
        <li>Continue with strength training to support muscle tone and overall strength.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        Always consult with your healthcare provider before starting any new exercise routine or making significant dietary changes.
    </p>

